  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Claude is not your architect. Stop letting it pretend",
      "url": "https://www.hollandtech.net/claude-is-not-your-architect/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48259784",
      "score": 257,
      "comments": 185,
      "author": "cdrnsf",
      "published": "2026-05-24T18:28:11Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs like Claude 3.5 Sonnet excel at localized code generation but lack the holistic reasoning needed for complex software architecture.",
        "Relying blindly on AI for system design leads to over-engineered microservices, flawed database schemas, and critical architectural drift.",
        "Deploy LLMs for tactical tasks like unit testing and boilerplate generation, leaving high-level structural decisions to human staff engineers."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "A Simple Makefile Tutorial",
      "url": "https://cs.colby.edu/maxwell/courses/tutorials/maketutor/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/owa9kn",
      "score": 6,
      "comments": 3,
      "author": "kenballus",
      "published": "2026-05-25T14:44:03Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Use .PHONY to prevent name conflicts with local files, ensuring targets like clean or test always execute reliably.",
        "Leverage automatic variables like $@ for target names and $< for the first prerequisite to write DRY, maintainable build rules.",
        "Implement automatic dependency generation using GCC/Clang -MMD flags to rebuild binary targets only when header files actually change."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "How my minimal, memory-safe Go rsync steers clear of vulnerabilities",
      "url": "https://michael.stapelberg.ch/posts/2026-05-24-minimal-memory-safe-go-rsync-vulns/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/5y9u93",
      "score": 79,
      "comments": 10,
      "author": "stapelberg",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:38:34Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Implementing rsync in Go eliminates classic C-based memory corruption bugs like buffer overflows and use-after-free vulnerabilities.",
        "A minimal rsync codebase reduces attack surface by omitting legacy protocol features and risky, complex command execution paths.",
        "Using Go's native path-cleaning libraries mitigates common rsync directory traversal vulnerabilities like those seen in CVE-2022-29154."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "Improving my self-hosted actions runner setup",
